title: Greek culture-the adventure of the human spirit.pdf
description:
G. Braziller | 1966 | Pdf | Eng | 381 pag | 58.8 MB

The Greek experience endures for Western man as one of endless fascination and  unparalleled relevance. The point of departure of Western consciousness, it is as well the matrix to which Western man returns periodically in self-renewal. For in Greece man encountered Man: he discovered the adventure of being human, the cosmic issues man must face, the problems of human relationships and the modes of human community
